Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Cut @Tomato{1} into wedges.

Place potatoes and half the @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #microwave-safe bowl{}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until almost tender, ~{4%minutes}. Keep covered.

Pat @Ranch Steak{10%ounce} dry and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot #stainless steel pan{}. Cook steak to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Add remaining garlic herb butter to pan and spoon over steak. Transfer steak to a #cutting board{}; reserve butter in pan.

Carefully remove plastic wrap from potatoes; transfer potatoes and any remaining butter from bowl to same pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fork-tender, about ~{2%minutes}.

In a second microwave-safe bowl, mix half the @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce} (all for 4), half the @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} (all for 4), and a big pinch of pepper. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave ~{40%seconds}.

In a third #bowl{}, toss @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, tomato, @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce}, @Greek Vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} (large drizzle for 4); season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Drizzle steak and potatoes with creamy mustard sauce. Serve with salad.